        "jsCode": "// Day Counter — weekday-based 90-day counter starting March 2, 2026\nfunction getWeekdayDates() {\n  const dates = [];\n  const d = new Date(Date.UTC(2026, 2, 2));\n  while (dates.length < 90) {\n    if (d.getUTCDay() !== 0 && d.getUTCDay() !== 6) dates.push(d.toISOString().split('T')[0]);\n    d = new Date(d.getTime() + 86400000);\n  }\n  return dates;\n}\nconst weekdays = getWeekdayDates();\nconst now = new Date();\nconst todayStr = now.toLocaleDateString('en-CA', { timeZone: 'Africa/Lagos' });\nlet dayNum = null;\nfor (let i = 0; i < weekdays.length; i++) {\n  if (weekdays[i] === todayStr) { dayNum = i + 1; break; }\n}\nconst watDay = new Date(todayStr + 'T12:00:00Z').getUTCDay();\nconst isWeekend = watDay === 0 || watDay === 6;\nconst weekNum = dayNum ? Math.ceil(dayNum / 5) : null;\nreturn [{ json: { day_number: dayNum, week_num: weekNum, is_weekend: isWeekend, date: todayStr } }];"
      },
